Subject: Re: [VB] questions about a bus find

the transmission won't last long being run backwards.  The R&P flip will
take care of the output, but the gears still run backwards.

Usually, a special cam was installed in the Corvair engine to allow the
engine to run backwards, or the Corvair transmission was installed with
the engine.

George

On Sun, 17 Feb 2002, cameron johnson wrote:

> I believe crown made those kits,they no longer make
> them or are out of business..if I am not mistaken
> corvair engines run backwards requireing the ring and
> pinion to be reversed or you will end up with 4
> reverse gears..so be leary about using that trans in
> another vw powered bus..
>
> -cameron
